    <h2 id="setup">Setting Up Chinese Input</h2>
    <p><strong>Windows:</strong> Settings → Time & Language → Language → Add Chinese (Simplified or Traditional). <strong>Mac:</strong> System Preferences → Keyboard → Input Sources → add Chinese. <strong>iPhone:</strong> Settings → General → Keyboard → Add Keyboard → Chinese. <strong>Android:</strong> Settings → System → Language & Input → add Chinese keyboard.</p>

    <h2 id="pinyin-typing">Pinyin Typing Tips</h2>
    <p>Type the pinyin without tone marks — the software shows matching characters. For example, type "nihao" and select 你好 from the suggestions. Type full words rather than single characters for better prediction accuracy. Most systems learn your preferences over time.</p>

    <h2 id="shortcuts">Useful Shortcuts</h2>
    <p>Switch between Chinese and English input with Ctrl+Space (Windows) or Caps Lock (Mac Chinese keyboard). Use the number keys to select from prediction lists. In WeChat and most apps, you can switch input methods within the keyboard. Practice by chatting with language exchange partners or writing social media posts. Use our <a href="/chinese/tools/pinyin-converter/">Pinyin Converter</a> if you need to check the pinyin for any character.</p>

